# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 01-hyv3-arch.patch — HY_V3 (hy_v3) base architecture support for llama.cpp
#
# Base commit : 19bba67c1f4db723c60a0d421aa0788bf4ddc699 (ggml-org/llama.cpp master, 2026-06-08)
#
# PROVENANCE / ATTRIBUTION
#   This patch is DERIVED FROM GrahLnn's community patch:
#     https://huggingface.co/GrahLnn/Hy-MT2-30B-A3B-4bit-GGUF/blob/main/patches/llama-cpp-hyv3.patch
#   The original targets an earlier llama.cpp (~commit 1506d39e7, 2026-05-25).
#   We rebased/adapted it onto 19bba67c1 (≈220 commits newer) and fixed three
#   drifts so it applies & compiles cleanly on this base:
#     • src/models/hyv3.cpp: n_layer is an accessor here -> hparams.n_layer()
#     • conversion/hyv3.py : HF config field is expert_hidden_dim (not moe_intermediate_size)
#     • src/llama-model.cpp: LLM_ARCH_HYV3 hand-merged into the NEOX rope group
#
# SPECIAL THANKS
#   Huge thanks to GrahLnn for the original hy_v3 llama.cpp patch — it did the hard
#   groundwork of getting the architecture into llama.cpp. This adaptation stands
#   entirely on that work. 🙏
#
# WHAT IT ADDS
#   The hy_v3 architecture (Tencent Hunyuan V3 MoE: GQA + Q/K-norm, sigmoid router
#   with correction bias, per-layer shared expert). Enough to convert HF -> GGUF
#   and run inference. NO MTP, NO tool/thinking parser (see 02-*.patch for those).
#
# APPLY
#   git apply 01-hyv3-arch.patch
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
